1 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a Statewide
2 Recovery Special Account for the Oklahoma Water Resources Board for
3 each appropriation section of this act. The duration of such
4 accounts shall continue for the period of time that monies related
5 to the American Rescue Plan Act of 2021 are being budgeted,
6 expended, or managed in the state. The ending of such period shall
7 be determined by the State Treasurer, and shall result in the
8 closing of such accounts as a matter of law. Such accounts shall be
9 continuing accounts as otherwise provided in this section, not
10 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall exclusively consist of
11 monies related to the relevant appropriations made in this act and
12 as otherwise directed by law. All monies deposited to the credit of
13 such accounts are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
14 expended by the Oklahoma Water Resources Board in accordance with
15 the provisions of this act. Expenditures from such accounts shall
16 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
17 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
18 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
19 B. The Oklahoma Water Resources Board is authorized to request
20 in writing that the monies appropriated by the provisions of this
21 act be deposited or transferred to the accounts created pursuant to
22 subsection A of this section. No later than seven (7) calendar days
23 from the date of such request, the Director of the Office of
24 Management and Enterprise Services shall comply with such request
